      "id": "imperative",
      "icon": "📣",
      "title": "Imperative",
      "subtitle": "L-Imperattiv: giving commands",
      "intro": "The imperative is what you use when you tell someone to do something. Two forms: singular (you alone) and plural (you all).",
      "facts": [
        "Singular form is for one person.",
        "Plural form adds -u on the end (or similar suffix).",
        "Tip: drop the first letter of the present-tense verb to get the imperative. nifhem (I understand) → ifhem (you understand!)."
      ],
